-- Honeywell sees higher 2008 profit
-- 
-- Thu Dec 13, 2007 7:19am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/13/us-honeywell-outlook-idUSWNAS448220071213

 

 BOSTON  (Reuters) - Diversified manufacturer Honeywell International Inc ( HON.N ) said on Thursday that it expected to report 2008 profit of $3.65 to $3.80 per share, up 16 percent to 21 percent from forecast 2007 earnings, on favorable macro trends and productivity improvements. 

 Analysts on average expect 2008 profit of $3.67 per share, according to Reuters Estimates. Honeywell reiterated its 2007 earnings estimate of $3.14 to $3.16 per share. The world's largest maker of cockpit electronics said it expected revenue to rise 5 percent to 7 percent next year. (Reporting by  Scott Malone ; Editing by Lisa Von Ahn)